1.1 Sample Data


The TeacherEvaluation dataset obtained from the Real Statistics Using Excel website by Charles Zaiontz was used for this illustrated example.

Preliminary dataset assessment:

[A] 120 rows (observations)

[B] 9 columns (variables)
[B.1] 9/9 descriptors = 9/9 ordered category
[B.1.1] EXP (Setting high expectations for the students)
[B.1.2] ENT (Entertaining)
[B.1.3] COM (Able to communicate effectively)
[B.1.4] MAS (Having mastery in their subject)
[B.1.5] MOT (Able to motivate)
[B.1.6] CAR (Caring)
[B.1.7] CHA (Charismatic)
[B.1.8] PAS (Having a passion for teaching)
[B.1.9] FRI (Friendly and easy-going)

  SecondModes <- function(x) {
    ux <- unique(na.omit(x))

                               uniqueCut = 10,

(DPA_LowVariance[DPA_LowVariance$nzv,])
## [1] freqRatio     percentUnique zeroVar       nzv          
## <0 rows> (or 0-length row.names)
if ((nrow(DPA_LowVariance[DPA_LowVariance$nzv,]))==0){
  
  print("No low variance descriptors noted.")
  
} else {

  print(paste0("Low variance observed for ",
               (nrow(DPA_LowVariance[DPA_LowVariance$nzv,])),
               " numeric variable(s) with First.Second.Mode.Ratio>4 and Unique.Count.Ratio<0.10."))
  
  DPA_LowVarianceForRemoval <- (nrow(DPA_LowVariance[DPA_LowVariance$nzv,]))
  
  print(paste0("Low variance can be resolved by removing ",
               (nrow(DPA_LowVariance[DPA_LowVariance$nzv,])),
               " numeric variable(s)."))
  
  for (j in 1:DPA_LowVarianceForRemoval) {
  DPA_LowVarianceRemovedVariable <- rownames(DPA_LowVariance[DPA_LowVariance$nzv,])[j]
  print(paste0("Variable ",
               j,
               " for removal: ",
               DPA_LowVarianceRemovedVariable))
  }
  
  DPA %>%
  skim() %>%
  dplyr::filter(skim_variable %in% rownames(DPA_LowVariance[DPA_LowVariance$nzv,]))

}
